1. Substitute the sonic point conditions $v_s = a_s$ and $a_s^2 =  rac{M}{2 r_s}$ into the Bernoulli equation:
 rac{ rac{M}{2 r_s}}{2} +  rac{ rac{M}{2 r_s}}{\gamma-1} -  rac{M}{r_s} =  rac{a_{\inf ty}^2}{\gamma-1}
 rac{M}{4 r_s} +  rac{M}{2(\gamma-1) r_s} -  rac{M}{r_s} =  rac{a_{\inf ty}^2}{\gamma-1}
2. Rearrange the equation by factoring out $ rac{M}{r_s}$ on the left side:
 rac{M}{r_s} \left(  rac{1}{4} +  rac{1}{2(\gamma-1)} - 1 ight) =  rac{a_{\inf ty}^2}{\gamma-1}
3. Combine the terms inside the parentheses over a common denominator $4(\gamma-1)$:
 rac{M}{r_s} \left(  rac{\gamma-1 + 2 - 4(\gamma-1)}{4(\gamma-1)} ight) =  rac{a_{\inf ty}^2}{\gamma-1}
 rac{M}{r_s} \left(  rac{5 - 3\gamma}{4(\gamma-1)} ight) =  rac{a_{\inf ty}^2}{\gamma-1}
4. Cancel the $\gamma-1$ term from both sides (since $\gamma > 4/3$, $\gamma-1 
eq 0$):
 rac{M}{r_s}  rac{5 - 3\gamma}{4} = a_{\inf ty}^2
5. Solve the algebraic equation for $\gamma$:
5 - 3\gamma =  rac{4 a_{\inf ty}^2 r_s}{M}
3\gamma = 5 -  rac{4 a_{\inf ty}^2 r_s}{M}
\gamma =  rac{5}{3} -  rac{4 a_{\inf ty}^2 r_s}{3 M}
